  "packageMaterializedConfigIsAuthoritative": true,
  "usageRules": [
    "Every newly generated application must include the Soft outline controls style as an Application Custom Control Style in decoded Themes[].",
    "Every newly generated application must clone this Type 1 style with a fresh package-local UUID instead of reusing the exported template UUID, then set the application default control style through a Type 0 application style theme whose Ext JSON controlDefaultId points to the fresh Type 1 style theme ID.",
    "Only package-local theme identity and style ID fields are remapped. Do not rewrite ordinary style tokens, color values, control configuration values, or other non-ID settings inside the style Config.",
    "Do not depend on tenant-global or system control style IDs for generated packages; the package must carry the Application Custom Control Style itself.",
    "Do not emit the style Config as an object. Yeeflow package export shape stores Theme.Config as a stringified JSON object.",
    "The Type 0 application style Config must be a stringified JSON object containing primary, secondary, neutral, and typography settings. Primary, secondary, and neutral must each store a base #RRGGBB color and lightmodel exactly equal to Luminance.",
    "The App Plan must select Primary, Secondary, and Neutral base colors. If the user provides approved brand colors, use those values when they pass readability ranges. If the user does not provide brand colors, infer a business-appropriate palette from the application purpose and write the rationale in the App Plan. Do not keep the generic defaults only because the user was silent.",
    "The generic fallback base colors in this template may be used only when the business domain cannot be inferred or when the user explicitly requests or approves the Yeeflow default palette. Success, warning, danger, background, text, and accent remain the standard Yeeflow semantic color system.",
    "Full-app upgrades must preserve this default style unless the user explicitly requests a different application control style."
  ],
